158
00:06:58,001 --> 00:07:00,035
I’d have filmed 10 episodes of my new show by now.

159
00:07:00,615 --> 00:07:02,628
Think what you want.

160
00:07:02,915 --> 00:07:04,448
But if your idea is bad,

161
00:07:04,461 --> 00:07:05,335
I won’t let it slide.

162
00:07:05,368 --> 00:07:07,121
I won’t let yours slide, either.

163
00:07:08,775 --> 00:07:09,775
Here.

164
00:07:10,115 --> 00:07:10,875
Two spoons of coffee,

165
00:07:10,895 --> 00:07:12,421
two and a half sugars, and one cream.

166
00:07:17,415 --> 00:07:20,755
You’re the only one this picky.

167
00:07:41,275 --> 00:07:43,275
(You’re watching Good Days.)

168
00:07:43,308 --> 00:07:47,768
(I’m Tae. Let me help you with the forecast.)

169
00:07:47,795 --> 00:07:50,055
(The weather is so hot right now.)

170
00:07:50,081 --> 00:07:52,528
But don’t let your head

171
00:07:52,561 --> 00:07:55,321
get as hot as the weather, guys.

172
00:07:55,348 --> 00:07:56,408
Hot, my ass!

173
00:08:01,335 --> 00:08:02,335
Ah, it’s hot!

174
00:09:51,295 --> 00:09:52,588
You want to work separately?

175
00:09:53,135 --> 00:09:54,201
Yes, Professor.

176
00:09:54,535 --> 00:09:56,148
We don’t really see eye to eye.

177
00:09:56,445 --> 00:09:58,495
Let each of us work on our own.

178
00:09:58,521 --> 00:09:59,521
Yes.

179
00:10:00,035 --> 00:10:04,068
But you’ll be evaluated on teamwork for this subject.

180
00:10:05,125 --> 00:10:06,021
I have an idea.

181
00:10:06,048 --> 00:10:08,288
If you can’t come to agreement,

182
00:10:08,328 --> 00:10:10,575
